Registry pound commands can take the following qualifiers after the registry name

    asAttributes    items loaded into the registry will be marked as attributes. This also changes the default behavior in which attributes are not loaded into a registry
    
    base            marks the registry as a base registry
    
    components      if this is not specified, only outermost blocks are loaded otherwise component blocks are loaded too
    
    data            registry will be populated from attributes. For example, if a block being loaded has an attribute: artist and artist is registered (ie, there is a registry named artist) then the value associated with the artist attribute (presumably the artists name) will be registered if not already in the registry.
    
    doNotCopy       if referring to a registry item in a group attribute, do not copy it. Normally,
                    registered items are copied when referenced.

    grouped         if an attribute is registered, when it is added to its associated block, the block is in turn added to the registered attribute, in effect making the attribute a group containing all the blocks with which it is associated
    
    hasMethods      when adding to the registry, check to see if the group added has a method (jit attribute) and if it does, compile it
    
    noMerging       do not merge any of the registry groups if they are referenced as attributes
    
    search          adds the registry to the registry search list
    
    tagged          When a tagged attribute is added to an item, the item gets added as
        a member of the tagged attribute
    
    value           by default, when a block gets loaded into a registry, its tag is the key. However, if the value qualifier is set, the block value as text is used as the key.
Mac fonts are stored in /Library/Fonts or /System/Library/Fonts
<fontList/>
<libraryFonts directory="/Library/Fonts" mask=~'[.]tt[cf]' into=fontList/>
<systemFonts directory="/System/Library/Fonts" mask=~'[.]tt[cf]' into=fontList/>
<supplementalFonts directory="/System/Library/Fonts/Supplemental" mask=~'[.]tt[cf]' into=fontList/>
#load libraryFonts;
#load systemFonts;

